## PR Description
**Title**: [rust-compiler] Demote type-only TS/Flow declarations to Unknown passthrough

**Body**:
## Summary

The 17 TS/Flow *type-only* declarations (`TSTypeAliasDeclaration`, `TypeAlias`, `Declare*`, etc.) are never structurally inspected by the compiler — it skips them in function bodies and preserves them verbatim at module level. Modeling them as typed `Statement` variants only added clone/serialize/deserialize code to the large `Statement` enum.

This demotes them to `Statement::Unknown` (RawNode passthrough), dispatched at lowering via a new `is_type_only_statement_tag`. The structs themselves stay (the `Declaration` enum still uses them for `export type` / `export interface`).

**Shrinks the release napi binary by ~191 KB (7,227,376 → 7,036,576 bytes, ~2.6%).**

Behavior is unchanged: the Rust-vs-TS port suite (1804/1 — the single failure is the pre-existing `fbt` `error.todo` fixture, identical to `main`; all 1805 code outputs match), the AST round-trip, and unit tests all pass.

