## PR Description
**Title**:   [react-devtools] AI chat assistant in the Profiler

**Body**:
## Summary

Profiling data is dense and hard to interpret, you can see *that* a commit was slow, but working out *why* (wasted renders, effect cost, what scheduled the update, what the user did to trigger it) takes expertise and manual digging. This PR adds an AI chat tab to the Profiler that answers those questions from the recorded session.

This is intentionally the **complete feature as a draft** so it can be tested end-to-end. If there's interest in landing it, I'll split it into a reviewable stack (e.g provider layer → chat UI + agent loop → profiler tools → interaction capture → perf-tracks capture).

## How did you test this change?

**Unit tests** (all green, `yarn test-build-devtools`): new tests covering the provider layer , the `console.timeStamp`
capture (pass-through, caps, stacking-safe restore), and the phase tools. `yarn prettier`, `yarn lint`, `yarn flow dom-node` clean.

**End-to-end, zero credentials needed** (local Ollama):
- `yarn build-for-devtools`
- `cd packages/react-devtools-extensions && yarn build:chrome`
- load chrome/build/unpacked via chrome://extensions (Developer mode)
- `OLLAMA_ORIGINS="chrome-extension://*" ollama serve   # any local model`
- You can use `qwen3-coder:30b` to confirm but still need larger model for better analysis.
- Codex subscription and Ollama Cloud also supported


